column10:
Man, what a great game. I can tell just by looking at it. The story, the characters, the design change, the battles, the suspense, the thrill, everything packed right here in this game. As if Xrd didn't wowed me enough... Strive did made my cradle rock. 

PROS:
- Diverse characters, each with their own unique fighting styles;
- A design change that we, fans, didn't know was possible;
- Ongoing DLCs (Elphelt came to rock with us!);
- Engaging and touching music;
- Story is complex and well written;
- In Arcade, you can fight characters that you don't have as DLCs yet (I got a chance to fight against Testament Extreme Route - oh, happy (chaos) me!);
- English vocals and translations for great understanding (Thank you!);
- The game has trading cards and achievements.

NEUTER:
- Found out how to reconfigure settings to allow me to play with Keyboard Arrows! Yes!

CONS:
- My game is slowing down (lagging) at times. Could be the drives or the FPS. But the difference between the visual and the keyboard input is mere 2 miliseconds, so it's not bad. 

NEUTER:
- Fought with a friend in a private room, he/she was absolutely stunned that I play Strive with this low performance frame rate. (Boy/Girl, you should have seen me playing GGXX Accent Core Plus emulated on a Win 7 - it was waaayyy slower than this!)

In conclusion, this game is outstanding. I recommend it to all Guilty Gear fans, especially to those that love a good fighting game and a great story.
